  "id": "CENTRAL-CODE-ON-WAGES",
  "name": "Code on Wages, 2019",
  "shortName": "Code on Wages",
  "officialCitation": "The Code on Wages, 2019 (Act No. 29 of 2019), operative from 21 November 2025.",
  "overview": "The Code on Wages, 2019 is the current central framework for minimum wages, payment of wages, statutory bonus and gender-based wage equality. It became operative on 21 November 2025. The Code on Wages (Central) Rules, 2026 apply where the Central Government is the appropriate government; State and Union Territory rules and notifications apply where another government has jurisdiction. Instruments under the repealed wage enactments continue only to the extent preserved by section 69 and until lawfully replaced or repealed.",
